  "body": "In ui & ui2 folder we have images as @2x.png and @3x.png.\r\nThey are high-quality png images and some of them like [onboarding](https://www.figma.com/file/o4qG1bnFyuyFOvHQVGgeFY/Onboarding-for-Mobile?node-id=5508%3A323380&t=PPuvxyHUMLozgW4F-0) images are quite big in size\r\n(@2x.png 4.8MB, @3x.png 9.1 MB)\r\n\r\nThese big image sizes keep adding up and affect metro bundler loading time and app size.\r\n\r\nWe should refactor imported images and improve size and performance.\r\nWe can look into a few questions like\r\n\r\n1. Do we need to add multiple formats or can we just add a single one? (and which one?)\r\n2. Should we use a jpeg instead?",
